title: The Duprees - All-Time Greatest Hits (320)
description:
The Duprees - All-Time Greatest Hits (320)

The Duprees were an Italian-American doo wop group that originated in New Jersey.  Their music consisted largely of updated versions of 1950s pre-rock era standards, reworking moldy oldies into more contemporary versions.  The height of their success came in 1962-63, making the top 40 with "Have You Heard" and "Why Don't You Believe Me", and the top ten hit, "You Belong to Me."  The Duprees were retro even at their peak, and though they continued to record through the sixties, they were largely forgotten during the British Invasion.
